      • create

        public static MetricWrapper2 create(Metric metric,
                                    Alg alg,
                                    int datasetId,
                                    xURI datasetUri)
                             throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Creating a metric wrapper with specified internal metric, algorithm name, identifier of dataset, URI of dataset, and algorithm description. This method is used to construct a metric wrapper.
        Parameters:
        metric - specified internal metric actually calculates measure for evaluating an algorithm.
        alg - specified algorithm on which the internal metric evaluates.
        datasetId - specified identifier (ID) of the dataset used to evaluate the algorithm.
        datasetUri - specified URI of the dataset used to evaluate the algorithm.
        Returns:
        new metric wrapper with specified internal metric, algorithm name, identifier of dataset, and URI of dataset.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - if any error raises.
